vernment at Westminster in 2017. This study will be invaluable to all interested in minority government and British political history, from policymakers, students, and journalists to the general public.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCoalition governmentszGreat Britain. 4aPolitical Studies 2020. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh  a1977-78 Lib-Lab Pact.  aBritish tradition.  aCallaghan Minority Governments.  aConservative Party.  aLabour Party.  aWestminster.  aWilson Minority Governments.  aearly elections.  ainternal government.  ainternational theory.  ainterparty coalitions.  aminority governance.  amyths.  aparty files.  apost-electoral plans.  astrategy-making processes.1 aPeacock, Timothy Noël, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packagez978311128277040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612327540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526123275423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526123275/original  a978-3-11-128277-0  Manchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packageb2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles